I can quite honestly say I haven’t enjoyed an album this much in a VERY long time. I take my hat off to tyler for producing such a diverse yet cohesive, happy yet sad, hype yet chill album this AMAZING. I love u so much @tylerthecreator and thank u for sharing ur heart with us x
jesus, that was a ride.

ARE WE STILL FRIENDS? pt2
...this is shown in the last two lines of the song: “can’t say goodbye”. throughout the song, he asks his ex to keep in touch and to not to be a stranger. while this seems innocent enough, it’s likely because he wants his love back again.

ARE WE STILL FRIENDS?
another favourite of the album, again mostly because it’s beautiful instrumentals. however, this song is a hint that tyler really doesn’t want it to be over between him and his ex, he misses them and wants them in his life...

I DON’T LOVE YOU ANYMORE
while this song seems like tyler is coming to terms with the break up and finally admitting he’s not in love anymore... I can’t help but feel he’s only trying to convince himself of this, when he actually still loves this person very much.

GONE, GONE / THANK YOU pt6
...while thanking his ex-partner for everything, tyler says “got my eye” which could be his way of saying that his eyes are finally open to the relationship being over and he can now move on from it all.

GONE, GONE / THANK YOU pt5
...this is how the ‘thank you’ portion of the song opens up. tyler is thanking his love for all the love and all the joy but expresses how he never wants to fall in love again. we’ve all been there, a heartbreak so deep it puts you off love entirely...

GONE, GONE / THANK YOU pt4
...and realising how jaded he had been by his love the whole time. the rose tinted glasses are a curse I’ve been victim to many times before, and I can confirm: it sucks. “I hate wasted potential, that shit crushes your spirit...it crushes your soul”...

GONE, GONE / THANK YOU pt3
...and that she won’t ever compete with tyler. the bitterness is something I relate to on a spiritual level. he wants his ex to be happy but knows he could do a better job than her. leading into the middle section tyler is coming to terms with it all...

GONE, GONE / THANK YOU pt2
“whether it’s rain or shine I know I’m fine for now, my love’s gone...or maybe it’s just a dream that I can’t seem to wake up from, my love’s gone” TELL ME THAT DIDN’T HURT YOU! he then goes on to say he hope’s his love’s new girl got taste...

GONE, GONE / THANK YOU
ok buckle up for about ten parts to this because not only is this the longest song on the album but the absolute BEST one. split into two (or three?) parts, tyler is accepting the end of the relationship after all the turmoil and it’s SO FUCKIN SAD...

WHAT’S GOOD pt2
it’s actually incredibly optimistic. “I see the light” could be a reference to tyler finally seeing behind the mask of his love interest. this is highlighted at the end of the song with “I don’t know what’s harder, letting go or just being ok with it”

WHAT’S GOOD 
ok so this is up there with one of my favourite tracks of the album. of course for its incredible beat and general HEAVY vibe, but after listening to the lyrics it gives a whole other dynamic to this seemingly aggressive song.

PUPPET pt2
...and he’s willing to do almost anything. he’s realised he is nothing without his love and he is the source of everything good. he’s fully aware of the toxicity of the situation, but he doesn’t care. he just needs his love back.

PUPPET
after wanting nothing to do with his love at the end of the last track, tyler changes his tune here. opening with “I wanna talk”. anyone who’s had a tricky relationship will know this series of events all too well. he asks what his love needs in order to take him back...

A BOY IS A GUN
this boy is dangerous, he’ll be the death of tyler. in addition to the gorgeous production, this song is a journey in itself as he wrestles with his emotions, eventually deciding to leave his love as he’s not good for him... or so we thought...

NEW MAGIC WAND
tyler really be getting tired of these games his boy been playing. he wants the girl out of the picture and his love interest all to himself. still he’s pleading his love not to leave him. even though he’s putting his foot down, he’s still terrified of being left.

RUNNING OUT OF TIME
it’s been speculated that tyler’s love interest is in fact a man who is ‘in the closet’, hiding behind a relationship with a woman. tyler repeated tells him to take off his mask. this song feels desperate, time is running out for them. emotionally? physically?

EXACTLY WHAT YOU RUN FROM YOU END UP CHASING 
“exactly what you run from, you end up chasing. like, you can't avoid, but just chasing it and just like trying. giving it everything that you can. there's always an obstacle”
this spoken word interlude speaks for itself really.

I THINK 
the sheer uncertainty of “I think I’m falling in love, this time I think it’s for real”. but throughout the song he’s just toying with it, he doesn’t know for sure. his fear of commitment is holding him back while his vulnerability is pushing him forward at the same time

EARFQUAKE pt2
I adore the rawness in the refrain: “don’t leave, it’s my fault / ‘cause when it all comes crashing down I’ll need you”. that shit hurted. I’ve been there and sometimes you stay with someone who isn’t good for you due to fear of life without them by your side.

EARFQUAKE
ok this is where the story really starts. tyler is deeply in love with this person - so much so that he relies on them for survival. begging them not to leave, blaming himself. I’m undecided if this is a toxic relationship or if tyler has really been a shitty boyfriend.

IGOR’S THEME
the opening track just emanates tyler energy, it makes me so happy. I remember hearing this for the first time and thinking “oh yeah he’s back” and just being unbelievably excited. it may not be the deepest lyrically (mostly grunts) but the production is exquisite.

ok now I’m gonna go through each song and share my feelings on them. not because anyone asked but because I want to and I don’t care if this doesn’t interest anyone but me. I’m in my feels and I need to get this all out.
tyler’s storytelling abilities have always been prevalent but this album really hit a new level. I felt every second of his emotional journey like it was my own.
it really took me on a journey. I felt my heart fill with love, get broken into little pieces and sellotaped back together again. I’m really sat here like an open wound from listening to MUSIC.
whether or not you like him, listen to him or have heard of him I encourage you to give igor a listen.
